<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D23206FFFE5CCF00C9FE43FE88" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8D19AB593206FFFE5CCF00C9FE43FE88" blockId="8.[166,1225,175,330]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Third antennal segment black (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3206FFFE5FC200D6FBEDFF0B" box="[982,1049,175,201]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[182,215,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[175,1235,174,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-350@7.[174,1235,174,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig.4. Cheilosia transcaucasia, male (a–c): a — dorsal view, b — frontal view of head, c — genitalia; C. variabili, male (d–f): d — lateral view, e — frontal view of head, f — genitalia; C. vulpina, male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — lateral view of head, i — genitalia. Рис. 4. Cheilosia transcaucasia, самец (a–c): a — вид сверху, b — голова, фронтальный вид, c — гениталии; C. variabilis, самец (d–f): d — латеральный вид, e — голова, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии; C. vulpine, самец (g–i): g — латеральный вид, h — голова, латеральный вид, i — гениталии." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449157/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3206FFFE583F00D6FBCEFF0B" box="[1067,1082,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">h</emphasis>
); face with distinct hairs occasionally only in lower part; parafacial relatively narrow; scutellum with long black bristles along posterior margin; these hairs longer than scutellum in male and longer than its half in female; legs black (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3206FFFE5E9B0176FD39FEEB" box="[655,717,271,297]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[182,215,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[175,1235,174,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-350@7.[174,1235,174,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig.4. Cheilosia transcaucasia, male (a–c): a — dorsal view, b — frontal view of head, c — genitalia; C. variabili, male (d–f): d — lateral view, e — frontal view of head, f — genitalia; C. vulpina, male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — lateral view of head, i — genitalia. Рис. 4. Cheilosia transcaucasia, самец (a–c): a — вид сверху, b — голова, фронтальный вид, c — гениталии; C. variabilis, самец (d–f): d — латеральный вид, e — голова, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии; C. vulpine, самец (g–i): g — латеральный вид, h — голова, латеральный вид, i — гениталии." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449157/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3206FFFE5ECD0169FD11FEEB" box="[729,741,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">g</emphasis>
); wing without dark spot medially; male genitalia as in (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC3206FFFE5D420156FE67FE8B" box="[342,403,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[182,215,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[175,1235,174,1051]" captionTargetId="figure-350@7.[174,1235,174,1051]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig.4. Cheilosia transcaucasia, male (a–c): a — dorsal view, b — frontal view of head, c — genitalia; C. variabili, male (d–f): d — lateral view, e — frontal view of head, f — genitalia; C. vulpina, male (g–i): g — lateral view, h — lateral view of head, i — genitalia. Рис. 4. Cheilosia transcaucasia, самец (a–c): a — вид сверху, b — голова, фронтальный вид, c — гениталии; C. variabilis, самец (d–f): d — латеральный вид, e — голова, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии; C. vulpine, самец (g–i): g — латеральный вид, h — голова, латеральный вид, i — гениталии." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449157" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449157/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B3206FFFE5D8A0149FE52FE8B" box="[414,422,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">i</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
